{"title": "Coconut crab with stone bass", "url": "http://www.bbc.co.uk/food/recipes/coconut_crab_with_stone_52229", "img": null, "description": "\n    Seared fillets of stone bass served up with crabs in a rich tamarind and coconut curry sauce.\n", "prep time": "less than 30 mins", "cook time": "10 to 30 mins", "serves": "Serves 4", "ingredients": [" 150g/5oz desiccated coconut", " 4 cloves", " 2 sprigs curry leaves, leaves picked", " 1 tsp turmeric", " 2 tbsp vegetable oil", " 2 onions, finely sliced", " 2 green chillies, finely sliced", " 2 tbsp tamarind paste", " 2 tbsp palm sugar", " 400ml/14fl oz coconut milk", " 300g/11oz fresh white crab meat, picked", " 2 tbsp coriander leaves, roughly chopped", " 1 lime, juice only", " 4 x 200g/7oz stone bass fillet, skin on", " salt and freshly ground black pepper", " 1 tbsp olive oil", " 1 tbsp coriander cress"]}